dismissalText.commentary: Lendl Simmons run out (Jadeja/†Patel) 78 (102b 8x4 1x6 155m) SR: 76.47

dismissalComment.html: Simmons won't carry his bat after all! He sweeps just wide of short fine leg, Jadeja mops up at fine leg and fires the throw to the keeper, Simmons turns around and risks the second run but he's well short

headshotImage.caption: Adrian Barath, player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Adrian Barath, player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: the bowler deserves all the credit for that one, Barath was circumspect from the very beginning with the away swinging delivery, Yadav tempted him into poking at another delivery which was pitched up outside off, he followed the movement, his feet were all over the place, edged and no doubts about that

Excellent take by Raina at third slip! Samuels isn't sure so he's waiting for the third umpire to take a look, Samuels was squared up at the crease, tried to work it to the on side, got a leading edge and Raina had to dive low to his right at third slip, he just about managed to get his hands under the ball, needed a few replays to confirm that

and West Indies slide further! Yadav deserves credit again for that wicket, pitches it up and swings it away, forces him to drive but Ramdin gets it to lob off the top half of the bat, easily taken at backward point by Jadeja

commentTextItems.html: and Jadeja does the honours and Rohit has the satisfaction of seeing India through! Short and pulled away past midwicket, India get a 2-0 lead

commentPostTextItems.html: The way Rohit and Kohli batted would suggest that this was a cakewalk but it wasn't so. Things could have been tougher for India had West Indies applied the pressure, perhaps attacked a bit more. The field was pushed back for the part-timers and it seemed like they were waiting for India to throw it away and panic. The Kohli-Rohit stand bodes well for India. It's ironic that these two are competing for the No.6 slot in Tests.

Had it not been for Rampaul's freaky 86 at No.10, this match would have been hopelessly one-sided. The crowd had a full game and certainly got their money's worth. One worry for India - the inability to bowl yorkers and finish things off with the ball when the opposition is beaten and down. Wasim and Waqar were experts at this.

Sammy: That last-wicket stand gave us a lot of inspiration. It shows the fight in this team. We just can't get over the line though. Sooner rather than later we can get that final push. We'll keep our head up and come strongly at the Indians again. Roach's had a tough six months with catches being dropped off him."

Sehwag: Our bowlers did fantastically with the new ball. It was an off day for Ashwin but Jadeja bowled well. Great innings by Rampaul. The day belongs to him. I tried all combinations to get him out. Rohit and Virat batted very maturely."

Kohli is the Man of the Match: Two centuries in two games at this venue but the pitches were different. This one needed more hard work. People love cricket here and they come out in thousands. Always great to bat with Rohit, we can learn to build partnerships. Always a pleasure to watch him bat. Not much of dew surprisingly. It was seaming around early on. I know the feeling when you go through a bad patch I hope to extend this good form."
That's it from us here. Thanks very much for joining us. The cricket never stops. We'll see you again very soon. Cheers.

low full toss on the off stump and he pushes it down to mid-off
full on the pads and worked away easily to long-on, he will retain the strike

dismissalText.commentary: Adrian Barath c †Patel b Yadav 0 (8b 0x4 0x6 8m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: the bowler deserves all the credit for that one, Barath was circumspect from the very beginning with the away swinging delivery, Yadav tempted him into poking at another delivery which was pitched up outside off, he followed the movement, his feet were all over the place, edged and no doubts about that

dismissalText.commentary: Marlon Samuels c Raina b Yadav 4 (8b 0x4 0x6 14m) SR: 50

dismissalComment.html: Excellent take by Raina at third slip! Samuels isn't sure so he's waiting for the third umpire to take a look, Samuels was squared up at the crease, tried to work it to the on side, got a leading edge and Raina had to dive low to his right at third slip, he just about managed to get his hands under the ball, needed a few replays to confirm that

headshotImage.caption: Vinay Kumar player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Vinay Kumar player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Darren Bravo c Ashwin b Vinay Kumar 13 (17b 2x4 0x6 30m) SR: 76.47

dismissalComment.html: spoke too soon about Bravo! Good length on the off stump and Bravo attempts to loft him from the crease and clear mid-on, the bat face turns a bit and he mistimes it, easy catch for Ashwin at mid-on, very soft dismissal

dismissalText.commentary: Danza Hyatt c †Patel b Vinay Kumar 0 (2b 0x4 0x6 3m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: (Hotel) Hyatt checks in and departs immediately! Very similar to Barath's dismissal, Vinay teases him outside the off stump, Hyatt really has to play at it because it was very close to the off stump, pokes at it and gets a thin edge to the keeper

dismissalText.commentary: Denesh Ramdin c Jadeja b Yadav 2 (11b 0x4 0x6 12m) SR: 18.18

dismissalComment.html: and West Indies slide further! Yadav deserves credit again for that wicket, pitches it up and swings it away, forces him to drive but Ramdin gets it to lob off the top half of the bat, easily taken at backward point by Jadeja

headshotImage.longCaption: Parthiv Patel player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Kieron Pollard c †Patel b Ashwin 35 (30b 3x4 2x6 32m) SR: 116.66

dismissalComment.html: Ashwin has his revenge but Pollard isn't happy with the decision! Gets forward to defend, the ball lobbed off the pads and Parthiv ran forward and took the catch, Ravi gave him out immediately, replays weren't conclusive as to whether the ball clipped the glove or not

dismissalText.commentary: Daren Sammy lbw b Jadeja 2 (8b 0x4 0x6 7m) SR: 25

dismissalComment.html: that's plumb and everyone knows it, Sammy stays back at the crease but the ball lands on off , holds its line and traps him in front of the stumps as he tries to flick it away

dismissalText.commentary: Andre Russell b Jadeja 11 (13b 2x4 0x6 13m) SR: 84.61

dismissalComment.html: through the gate! Jadeja fires this flatter, the ball keeps a bit low and Russell tries to whack it over the on side, misses it completely

headshotImage.caption: Parthiv Patel player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Parthiv Patel player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Lendl Simmons run out (Jadeja/†Patel) 78 (102b 8x4 1x6 155m) SR: 76.47

dismissalComment.html: Simmons won't carry his bat after all! He sweeps just wide of short fine leg, Jadeja mops up at fine leg and fires the throw to the keeper, Simmons turns around and risks the second run but he's well short

image.longCaption: Kemar Roach player portrait, West Indies media day

dismissalText.commentary: Parthiv Patel c Sammy b Roach 2 (6b 0x4 0x6 5m) SR: 33.33

dismissalComment.html: first blood to Roach! He lands it on a good length outside off and gets it to shape away, Parthiv pokes at it and the outside edge goes low to Sammy at second slip, just manages to scoop it up

headshotImage.longCaption: Virender Sehwag player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Virender Sehwag player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Virender Sehwag player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Virender Sehwag c Russell b Samuels 26 (35b 3x4 0x6 71m) SR: 74.28

dismissalComment.html: there's a hush around the ground! Sehwag stays at the crease and he lofts inside out, he got quite a bit of elevation but not enough to clear Russell at wide long-off, he judges it well close to the boundary

headshotImage.longCaption: Adrian Barath, player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Gautam Gambhir c Barath b Rampaul 12 (18b 2x4 0x6 24m) SR: 66.66

dismissalComment.html: take that! Gambhir is in disbelief! It was wide and asking to be slashed, he reached out and tried to carve it over the packed infield but little Barath timed his leap very well and plucked it with one hand in the region of short cover

headshotImage.caption: Ravi Rampaul player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Ravi Rampaul player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Virat Kohli c †Ramdin b Rampaul 117 (123b 14x4 0x6 154m) SR: 95.12

dismissalComment.html: too bad he couldn't stay till the end! Kohli makes a bit of room to smash that down the ground but gets a feather edge to Ramdin, too late for Windies though, Kohli walks back cross with himself but he needn't be, it was another responsible innings from him, very pleasing to watch

dismissalText.commentary: Rohit Sharma not out 90 (98b 7x4 2x6 131m) SR: 91.83

image.caption: Kemar Roach player portrait
image.longCaption: Kemar Roach player portrait, West Indies media day

dismissalText.commentary: Suresh Raina c †Ramdin b Roach 0 (1b 0x4 0x6 3m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: that's another one back in the pavilion! Raina gets a short ball straight up, he gets across to pull but it's a very half-hearted shot, feather edge and Ramdin and Roach know they've got their man

dismissalText.commentary: Ravindra Jadeja not out 9 (8b 1x4 0x6 13m) SR: 112.5
